verbose_text: Only males showed differences across genotypes in transferrin saturation levels (100% of homozygotes versus 37.5% of compound heterozygotes with transferrin saturation> 50%; p = 0.003), serum ferritin levels (77.8% versus 33.3% with serum ferritin> 300 ng/ml; p = 0.006), and diabetes (44.7% versus 28.0%; p = 0.03).
